The paper deals with optimization of cooperative relaying over slow fading channels, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of quantize-map-and-forward (QMF) relaying is a key aspect of the paper, which is a technique that is commonly used in wireless communication systems and falls under the signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of universal quantizers that use only the information of network topology, which is a topic that falls under the computer communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
